14) Create YOY Pointer And Format YOY color 21

STEP 1: Create a YoY Pointer.


      1. Create New Measure :     

                                   .YOY rev Arrow =  var Up = UNICHAR(9660)
                                                           var Down = UNICHAR(9650)
                                                           return
                                                           if( [.YoY]>[.YOY LY], Up, Down)

     2. Double click on a  card visual.

     3. Card visual will display on the report

     4. Drag and Drop the  ".YOY rev Arrow" to the Fields Box

     5. Select Format.

     6. Select General, Change the following:   X position : 0       Y position: 253      Width: 70     Height:  65       

     7.  Turn Off  category.

     8. Turn Off Background.



STEP 2: Format the pointer color 

   1. Create a new measure:        

              .YOY rev Arrow Condition =  if([.YoY]>[.YOY LY], 1,0)

    2. Select the Pointer card.

    3. Go to format .

    4.  Select Data label .

    5. Select Fx button.


 

   6. Follow This configuration Bellow to get

Red Down triangle      Green Up triangle  



STEP 3: Configure YOY Data Color.

   1. Select the YOY card.

   2. Select Format.

   3. Select data label.

   4. Select Fx button.


   

   5. Follow these steps bellow to configure.



Make sure every think works:


year  2007 is green 



Year 2008 is red
